
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        EXPOSE Instruction
                    Nginix Server Custom Banner

1.  Create custom banner in html subdirectory.

    $ cat html/index.html
    <html>
    <body>
    <h1>Hello from Docker!</h1>
    </body>
    </html>

2.  Make sure you are in the nginx directory (Important!)

3.  Run detached webserver container. 
    Use -v (volume option) to make index.html available to nginx.
    Map port 80 in container to port 5678 on host.

    $ docker run -d --name webserver \
    -v "$(pwd)"/html:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro -p 5678:80 nginx
 
4.  Show ports for webserver container.

    $ docker port webserver
    80/tcp -> 0.0.0.0:5678

5.  Show HTML with curl localhost and port.

    $ curl localhost:5678
    <html>
    <body>
    <h1>Hello from Docker!</h1>
    </body>
    </html>

6.  Show in browser with URL.

    http://localhost:5678

7.  Cleanup

    $ docker stop webserver
    $ docker container prune -f
